  "deviations": [
    "The existing LogUp engine requires at least two leaves; final_norm_rsqrt therefore pads 1 logical row to 2 (not the analytic 1), using the public LnRsqrt(0) pad pair.",
    "Router route-weight requant is an explicit existing Range(8) site (+28 logical/+32 padded rows and +2 sites); the analytic row named router_topk_range covered the comparison limbs but not this proved product requant.",
    "Router exp denominators add 8 authenticated values/layer so the exp rowsum is connected rather than isolated.",
    "Non-power-of-two Q/K/V slices use explicit public-weight openings; they are not treated as contiguous MLE halves. The synthetic seven-token embedding commitment pins vocabulary row 7 to zero as its canonical low-subcube pad row.",
    "Every synthetic weight block fits inside one P4_LAYER explicit row and is embedded in a distinct row; its source MLE point is extended to 14 variables with public-zero high coordinates, matching the closed X1 outer-padding construction without changing PCS parameters or semantics.",
    "One response-level PCS opening session contains three sequential existing MultiOpen proofs, one per D3 commitment, to keep peak CPU-VM memory bounded; this is reported explicitly rather than counted as one component proof.",
    "Reuses the existing P4 reciprocal-input floor deviation: recip_in = denom >> recip_den_shift is native-asserted while denominator rowsums, both vectors, and reciprocal LUT membership are authenticated/proved."
